org.apache.xml.security.utils.ElementProxy.length(String namespace, String
localname) is supposed to return the number of child elements with the specified
tag and namespace URI. However, instead it ignores the namespace. Diffs for
fix below:
Index: ElementProxy.java
===================================================================
--- ElementProxy.java   (revision 368871)
+++ ElementProxy.java   (working copy)
@@ -472,7 +472,7 @@
            while (sibling!=null) {
                if (localname.equals(sibling.getLocalName())
                                &&
-                                       namespace!=sibling.getNamespaceURI() ) {
+                                       namespace==sibling.getNamespaceURI() ) {
                        number++;
                }
                sibling=sibling.getNextSibling();

This cause some signatures with exclusive c14n transforms with inclusive
namespace parameters to validate incorrectly, because the Exclusive C14N
Transform implementation depends on the above method to parse the prefixList
parameter.
